âœ… Swift Best Practices
    â€¢    Use Swift Concurrency (async/await) for networking.
    â€¢    Use Result for error handling when necessary.
    â€¢    Avoid force unwrapping and use optional chaining and guard statements.
    â€¢    Avoid logic in Views, push all logic to ViewModels.
    â€¢    Leverage @StateObject, @ObservedObject, @EnvironmentObject for state.
    â€¢    Use Protocol-Oriented Programming where applicable.

