ğŸ“± Responsive Design
    â€¢    Use GeometryReader carefully. Avoid broken UIs and large blank spaces.
    â€¢    Test UI in Xcode Previews and multiple devices.
    â€¢    Use ScrollView where appropriate to handle smaller screen sizes.
    â€¢    Respect Safe Areas on all screens.

â¸»

âš™ï¸ Performance and Optimization
    â€¢    Use .lazy views (LazyVStack, LazyHStack) for large content.
    â€¢    Memoize views with @ViewBuilder and @MainActor.
    â€¢    Limit use of onAppear, onChange, Task {} in views.
    â€¢    Use async image loading when adding user photos.
    â€¢    Optimize for launch speed and minimize main thread tasks.

â¸»

ğŸ”’ Security and Data
    â€¢    Store preferences in UserDefaults for non-sensitive data.
    â€¢    Use Supabase authentication with secure tokens.
    â€¢    Validate all user inputs.
    â€¢    Use HTTPS endpoints only.
    â€¢    No sensitive data should be stored unencrypted on-device.

